Show HN: Meet Odin! – An AI-TPM designed to help engineering teams
text:
Preview: https://chat.setori.ai Video: https://youtu.be/Xzu4rIa783Y

AI-Feedback loops are in:

- Sensors: Put a sensor where you need it. - Data pipeline: Connect the data to an AI-system - Decision Making: Use the feedback for continuous optimization. - Actuation: Implement the decision

Alexander Sergeev and Paul Mikesell at https://lnkd.in/gibc7DiA serve as a phenomenal example of this. They own the sensor, the pipeline, the decision making and the actuation.

1/ What do AI-Feedback loops look like for Engineering Teams?

Imagine sailing full speed ahead, with your sails billowing as the wind drives your ship forward, knowing that your ship is fully prepared and operating at peak performance.

2/ Meet Odin! - The Ultimate Engineering Ally An AI-driven solution designed to help engineering teams be happier and focus on building by providing helpful real-time diagnostics, insights and interventions using combined data from Github, Jira/Linear, Calendar, Email & Slack.

We don’t have to imagine what this looks like. The Setori team has been hard at work on this for the past year and by combining our engineering command center with GPT4, we've built Odin and its something early adopters are already loving.

Preview here: setori.ai

Let me know what feedback you all have. Happy to answer questions.

Tell Hacker News: Pipl.com Silently adds a $500 monthly minimum for API Use
text:
I got email from Pipl support to re-check my use case and ensure it is inline with their acceptable use policy [1], after explaining what I used the product for they dropped this in the same email thread with no other context.

>Thank you for providing that information! I do want to advise that there is now a $500 monthly minimum in place for all of our API customers. If you do not perform the required number of queries each month to bring you to the $500 threshold, you will still be charged the full $500. If you are okay with this, we can accept a written consent over email and I will have our billing team put that minimum in place so you can continue to use our API.

They used to have no minimum and you would be billed per use monthly. It looks like they have removed all mention of pricing from there website as well. You can see other sites have captured the price [2].

I have no problem with a minimum for a service like this, but $0 to $500 per month is outlandish.

[1] https://pipl.com/resources/privacy-documents/pipl-permissible-use

[2] https://www.saasworthy.com/product/pipl/pricing

I need your help. I'm having a hard time wrapping my head around ChatGPT
text:
Background: I work in Compliance and have for 8-years.

A while back, I saw that there was a need, in Compliance, for people who know data analytics and who can build out systems that prevent and detect corporate wrongdoing.

I decided to pursue a bachelors in Data Analytics for this reason. I have about a year and a half-ish left.

But my mind is having a hard time reconciling my pursuit of a data analytics bachelor's degree with the capabilities of ChatGPT. I keep reading real, legitimate stories of how ChatGPT was able to all-together replace programmers for projects like developing micro services, websites, etc.

I understand that programmers still need to validate the code, and I'm not saying I even understand to what degree programmers are being replaced, but I can't help but feel like my pursuit of a formal bachelor's degree or even continuing to learn data analytics and data engineering will be in vain in light of what feels like major overnight advances in AI.

I wholeheartedly will appreciate your thoughts, insights, and time!

Thank you, and God bless.
